The paper proposes a deep learning method for traffic flow forecasting, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and gated recurrent units (GRUs) with an attention mechanism. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of CNNs, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) applications, and GRUs, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.NE) applications. Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data, which suggests that it may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
